Co.; 2009 N.Y. Misc. LEXIS 2182</ref><ref>Mitev, Vesselin. "Antidepressant Withdrawal Is Blamed for Assault." New York Law Journal. 11 Sept 2009. Available at: http://www.law.com/jsp/article.jsp?id=1202433728708&slreturn=1&hbxlogin=1</ref><ref>Michelle P. LaBaer v Pfizer, Inc. No.294236V. Circuit Court for Montgomery County Maryland.</ref> [[analgesic|analgesic medications]] (including [[opioid]]s),<ref name="Voreacos" /><ref>Daniel B. Timmons v The Purdue Pharma Company; Purdue Pharma LP; The Purdue Frederick Company; The P.F. Laboritories Inc.; The Abbott Laboratories; Abbott Laboratories, Inc. and Mallinckdrodt Inc. 8:04-CV-1479-T-26MAP. US District Court for the Middle District of Florida.</ref> and a range of [[mental disorder|psychiatric illnesses]].<ref>Friedman. Opinion re:Brobst v Workers Compensation Appeal Board Schuylkill Products Inc[Online]. 23 May 2003[accessed 18 Jul 2011]. Available at: http://caselaw.findlaw.com/pa-commonwealth-court/1426141.html.</ref><ref>Keen, Judy. "Legal Battle Ends Over Stuttering Experiment." USA Today.26 Aug 2007[accessed 18 Jul 2011]. Available at: http://www.usatoday.com/news/nation/2007-08-26-stuttering_N.htm</ref> Kruszewski has been recognized as a “distinguished expert” by [[senior status|senior]] [[federal judge]], [[Jack B. Weinstein|the Honorable Jack B. Weinstein]], [[United States District Court for the Eastern District of New York]] (June 2007).<ref name="Weinstein" /> He has been recognized as a psychiatric expert by [[Patti B. Saris|the Honorable Patti B. Saris]] and testified in the Federal Daubert hearings in US District Court of Massachusetts (May 2009).<ref>Saris, USDJ. "In Re Neurontin Marketing, Sales Practices, and Products Liability Litigation: This Document Relates to: All Products Liability Actions" Mdl No 1629 Civ Action No 04-10981-PBS (United States District Court, District of Massachusetts)</ref> Honorable Judge Rhonda E. Fischer has also accepted and affirmed expert testimony by Kruszewski in th